ca.corefacility.gview.layout.prototype
Interface SequencePoint

All Known Implementing Classes:
SequenceOffset, SequencePointImp
public interface SequencePoint

A point in terms of sequence coordinates (base, heightFromBackbone). Base is the base on the dna sequence (0 is zero base, 100 is 100th base/letter on gene, etc). heightFromBackbone is the height for the central part of the sequence. For linear, it coressponds to y-coords, for circular it's the radius.

Author:
Aaron Petkau
